## Branching — non-negotiable

| Action | Branch |
|--------|--------|
| **Daily audit / test / fix** | **`develop`** |
| **Create fix branches from** | **`develop`** |
| **Open PRs against** | **`develop`** — as **drafts**; never merge them yourself |
| **Go live** | Founder promotes **`develop` → `main`** after testing; you do not promote unless explicitly asked |
| **Parity** | Each run: `git rev-list --left-right --count origin/develop...origin/main` — report skew |

After a successful promote, **`develop` and `main` should be the same application** (only docs or release commits may differ briefly).

---

## Your job (every engagement)

Find what can go wrong for **riders**, **drivers**, and **admins** before users hit it. Investigate and report. Do not change production data without approval. Open a **draft PR to `develop`** only for clear bug fixes.

### Step 0 — Sync for audit

```bash
git fetch origin develop main
git checkout develop && git pull origin develop
```

Audit the **integration** codebase on `develop`. Run automated gates from this tree.

### Step 0b — Parity

```bash
git rev-list --left-right --count origin/develop...origin/main
```

Report in summary: **develop ↔ main parity** and **promote readiness**.

### Step 1 — Automated gates

From repo root (on `develop`):

```bash
npm run audit:daily
```

If any step fails, treat severity as **RED** and explain in your report.

### Step 2 — Playbook

Read `docs/DAILY_AUDIT_PROMPT.md` and work Phases 2–9 relevant to the task (skip DB queries if no read-only access — note that). **Every daily run must include Phase 3b § E–F** (scheduled solo + coworker group).

### Step 3 — Daily focus areas

- **RIDERS:** signup → verify → admin approve → book → pay → complete → receipt; **scheduled + coworker group rides**
- **DRIVERS:** doc upload → admin approve → go online → accept → complete → get paid; **group scheduled claim**
- **MAPS / PICKUP / DROPOFF:** geocode, live map, arriving → in_progress → complete
- **NOTIFICATIONS:** WebSocket, scheduled urgency, push/email
- **SAFETY:** SOS, emergency incidents, guardian links (`PUBLIC_APP_URL`)
- **PAYMENTS:** `/health/ready` stripe, webhooks, stuck `payment_status`
- **INFRA:** `peoplegoverned.com` DNS, Railway deploy health, **develop/main skew**

### Step 4 — Report format

Use the template in `docs/DAILY_AUDIT_PROMPT.md` § Required report format (includes parity + promote readiness).

Tag findings: `[RIDER]` `[DRIVER]` `[ADMIN]` `[PAYMENT]` `[SAFETY]` `[INFRA]`  
Severity: **P0** (today) · **P1** (user-blocking) · **P2** (degraded)

### Step 5 — If you fix code

```bash
git fetch origin develop && git checkout develop && git pull
git checkout -b cursor/<descriptive-name>-a737
# implement → npm run check → npm test → commit → push
```

Open a **draft PR: base = `develop`**, head = your branch. **Do not merge it yourself.**

